I'm a student myself living in Canada and all my life I've been sheltered from what most of you have served or been through, to me this was the myth of the Vietnam war.   Only a few months back that recieved the chance to experience or try to understand what went on behind the scenes, perhaps the untold stories.  It was an accident that I fell apone these vet's but today I am truely greatful for them all, they have been very close to my heart.  I have a deep respect and admiration for the courage that you have, and the pain that you've seen.  I know that I can never say I understand because I wasn't there, but what I can say is to never stop speaking your mind, tell your stories and your fears, educate your children's children,  bring out your past because once you have left this world my generation will need to speak out for you and pass on your thoughts as you left them to be said.  We need your words to help us all.<br>
May God bless you. Peace. 
